Add dllexport to make libsimulator can be compiled as dynamic library.
Fix some irregular implementation, function implement in simulator project, but use in libsimulator project

@ricardoquesada @minggo @pandamicro Please review this pr.

There a lot of hardcoded constants inside of ScrollView source code.

```
static const int NUMBER_OF_GATHERED_TOUCHES_FOR_MOVE_SPEED = 5;
static const float OUT_OF_BOUNDARY_BREAKING_FACTOR = 0.05f;
static const float BOUNCE_BACK_DURATION = 1.0f;

#define MOVE_INCH            7.0f/160.0f
```

```
Vec2 ScrollView::calculateTouchMoveVelocity() const
{
    float totalTime = 0;
    for(auto &timeDelta : _touchMoveTimeDeltas)
    {
        totalTime += timeDelta;
    }
    if(totalTime == 0 || totalTime >= 0.1f)
    {
        return Vec2::ZERO;
    }
```

If you don't want to give a chance to change it, at least you could give a way to use them from the outside, by moving it's declarations to header.
